Setup Part 1
------------------------
Add JavaFX SDK Libraries
------------------------
Download the JavaFX 16 SDK for your machine
	https://gluonhq.com/products/javafx/

1.  Right click on your Project > Build Path > Configure Build Path...
2.  Click on Libraries tab
3.  If you see JavaFX select it and click Edit... jump to step 5, then 8 to locate the files on your computer
	If you don't see JavaFX click Add Library...
4.  Click User Library > Next 
5.  Click on User Libraries...
6.  Click New...
7.  Enter "JavaFX" > do not check the box, click OK
8.  Click Add External Jars
9.  Locate and select all the jar files from JavaFX 16 lib folder
10. Select Apply and Close, Finish, Apply and Close
11. You should see the JavaFX library

Setup Part 2
-----------------------
Setup Runtime Arguments
-----------------------
1.  Open main.java
2.  Click on: 
		Run > Run Configurations...
3.  Click on tab
		(x)=Arguments
4.  In the box VM enter the following without quotes
		"--module-path C:\path_to_your_javaFXsdk\lib --add-modules=javafx.controls"
		where "path_to_your_javaFXsdk" is where you unzipped the JavaFX SDK on your computer.
		
